\begin_layout Problem
Aggregation.
 (You need to refer to Chapter 4 of the MWG for some literals of this question.
 Read that chapter.).
 Consider the following random consumer.
 There are two commodities, 
\begin_inset Formula $L=2$
\end_inset

, and prices and income will be strictly positive 
\begin_inset Formula $p>>0$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $w>0$
\end_inset

.
 There is a continuum of individuals and their choices will satisfy Walras'
 law.
 Consider the random consumption 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}$
\end_inset

, this is a well-behaved absolutely continuous, random variable, with finite
 first and second moment.
 The random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}$
\end_inset

 has a well-behaved distribution function 
\begin_inset Formula $F(x_{1})$
\end_inset

 defined over 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}\in\mathbb{R}_{+}$
\end_inset

, the density function is 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x_{1})>0$
\end_inset

 only if 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}\in\mathbb{R}_{+}$
\end_inset

.
 The distribution of random consumption variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}$
\end_inset

 does not depend on prices or income.
 Analogous to 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}$
\end_inset

, the consumption of good 
\begin_inset Formula $2$
\end_inset

 is governed by the random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 With probability 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

, for any realization of 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1},X_{2}$
\end_inset

, it must be that:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Problem
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Prob(p_{1}X_{1}+p_{2}X_{2}=w)=1.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Problem
The particular model we consider is one, where 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}$
\end_inset

 is realized, taking values on the interval 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq x_{1}\leq\frac{w}{p_{1}}=\boldsymbol{x}_{1}^{max}$
\end_inset

.
 Then the realizations of 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{2}$
\end_inset

 are fully determined as it must be that 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{2}=\frac{w-p_{1}x_{1}}{p_{2}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Problem

