\begin_layout Problem
(Too much choice/Choice overload) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Propose a model for consumer behavior that captures the following stylized
 fact.
 Consumer are more likely to choose an outside option (that we equate in
 this problem to not choosing) when the size of the menu is too big.
 Hint: The choice set is 
\begin_inset Formula $X\cup\{o\}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $o$
\end_inset

 is an outside option (not in 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

).
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 be finite.
 Menus are of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $A\cup\{o\}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $A\subseteq X$
\end_inset

, i.e., the outside option is always available to the consumer.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
You should describe with words what is the consumer choice algorithm, then
 you should describe what is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

new
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 in your model and how that relates to some behavioral or bounded rationality
 feature we learned in class, finally you should write the behavioral maximizati
on problem and show how your new model predicts the fact that when the menu
 size is large the consumer chooses the outside option.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
You should try to explain the model to me in the best way you can, by using
 words, diagrams and examples.
 However, you should have some formality, make the effort to write down
 the model using math, this is the only way to get full credit.
 
\end_layout

